ti = tissue elasticity, and i = √−1. The computer-controlled piston applies a 1.25 to 8-s perturbation to the lungs consisting of priming frequencies from 1 to 20.5 Hz. Multiple linear regression is used to fit impedance spectra derived from measured pressure and volume changes to the constant phase model of the lung.
